  tags = '{"teacher preferences","Chair 1","Chair 4","casters","desk configuration","lightweight","mobility","stability","FFE","furniture pilot","classroom reset","classroom management"}',
  searchable_text = $$Chair 4 was the top teacher pick for student chairs. Teachers T2 and T3 preferred Chair 4, 2 of 5 teachers. Reason: lightweight, easy to move, quiet on floors. Chair 1 was the runner-up for student chairs. Teachers T6 and T7 preferred Chair 1, 2 of 5 teachers. Reason: wide, stable, backpack hook. 2 casters was the preferred desk configuration. Teachers T2, T3, and T6 preferred 2 casters, 3 of 5 teachers. Reason: balance between mobile and stable. Teachers rearrange desks in 4 of 5 classrooms.$$,
  conclusions = '{"Teachers preferred Chair 4 for students due to its lightweight design and quiet movement on floors","Chair 1 was the teacher runner-up, valued for width, stability, and the backpack hook","3 of 5 teachers preferred 2 casters on desks as the best balance between mobility and control","Teachers rearrange desks in 4 of 5 classrooms, making desk mobility a practical daily priority"}'
